&lt;h3&gt;ABOUT THE ROLE&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our ideal candidate is a multifaceted individual. You should be a big thinker who fully understands what it takes to develop great brand centered creative. We expect an excellent standard of execution from any graphic designer joining our team. As a Designer, you look forward to working closely with multiple disciplines across the firm such as Strategy, Creative, Account and Marketing. You are fluent in ‘brand’ and comfortable with ‘strategy’ conversations. As such, you rise to the challenge of translating brand strategy into powerful and purposeful graphic design concepts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition, we are in search of an ideas person, an experimenter, someone who likes to develop concepts and tackle tricky problems. As a part of your concepting process, you are willing to challenge yourself and others, and bring unexpected connections to the table that inspire new ideas and ways of thinking.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Studio culture is critical to us. You are a creative who is a proactive self-starter, articulate, pragmatic and reliable. Someone who is happy to challenge our thinking and motivated to positively impact our design studio environment and graphic design community.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;YOUR DAY TO DAY&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work in partnership with project and account teams to understand client needs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to design projects from conception through delivery, including the design of brand guidelines and activation materials&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Produce outstanding design solutions across multiple touchpoints e.g. for comprehensive brand launches and/or brand campaigns&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to a lively office culture that encourages you to take an active role, experiment and grow as a designer&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interface credibly and effectively with clients for presentations&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay up-to-date with industry developments and design tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT YOU BRING&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2+ years of proven experience as a Designer, Graphic Design or similar role&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Portfolio of completed, brand design projects in response to client RFPs preferred&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Skills in Illustrator, InDesign, Photoshop, PowerPoint and Figma&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Nice to have skills in After Effects, InVision, Midjourney and Google Suite&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;BFA in Graphic Design preferred, or equivalent experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A solid understanding of typography, design elements and principles, and best practices across print and digital&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent interpersonal and communication skills, including solid verbal and written presentation skills&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attention to visual details while maintaining big picture overview of deliverables&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to manage own time and workflow in collaboration with a team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
